{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a5ee5b57-70a1-42dc-a2a7-8a2717710092","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.\n\nFixing the order:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_UYRE0bIM5c0NC2JaLLULaM","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9aa3e45375e94bccb10d478575f20837/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9aa3e45375e94bccb10d478575f20837/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"106c1ce6-2cee-4738-b1a5-8ae75f948623","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` has `open BrokenOrder.Domain`, which means it depends on `Domain.fs`. Since `Domain.fs` is listed *after* `Services.fs`, the compiler hasn't seen it yet when compiling `Services.fs`, causing a build failure.\n\n\nThe solution is straightforward - I need to move `Domain.fs` before `Services.fs` in the project file so the domain types are available when the services are compiled.","outputTokens":491,"requestId":"F030:1EDE:23A0F4:2A4752:69F93E97"},"id":"b6bad280-de3e-44ba-a590-33959b0c3f0d","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:49:35.732Z","parentId":"24f8f1eb-2722-4b1e-a33f-301d90312ff3"}
